The paper deals with the analysis of social graphs using tree decomposition (TD) heuristics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also discusses the identification and extraction of structures in social graphs, which falls under the category of cs.SD (Software Development). The use of TDs in scientific computing and structural graph theory is also mentioned, which suggests the category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses the correlation between TDs and demographic metadata, which falls under the category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper provides empirical results and suggests future directions for improved TD heuristics, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning).
